metadata.name: Leviathan #12
metadata.description:
Leviathan is a generative collection of large bodies made form particles, materialised from the viewers own subconscious. Atoms form gargantuan objects - subatomic monoliths and microscopic giants. Playing with the sense of scale it draws on the viewer’s subjective way of associating forms, a pattern that becomes a mirror, a skeleton for them to project. 

Part artist, part viewer. Leviathan asks us to question these relationships of creation, ownership and meaning. It is a chemical reaction that the artist starts and you finish. A colossal dream we are all sharing together - a leviathan.


Controls:
s or double tap: Download image
1 : Download 2400 x 4000
2 : Download 3600 x 6000
3 : Download 4800 x 8000
4 : Download 7200 x 12000

metadata.name: Morixel Colab #7 Generative Mirza #98
metadata.description:
This series is an interactive character creation project with the audience using computer programming. 
Thus, every time the Collector presses the create button on the site, a new character is born in the form of a member of the updated family of Qajar and this paradox of tradition and modernity provides a humorous atmosphere. which makes him smile and this event is our most important request.

If you like, give a name to your character and share it with us

The Generative Mirza is unique random Generated 200 PFP NFTs. The number of Traits in this collection is 10 (89 layers) and it has the ability to make unique 606,528,000 NFTs.

To create balance, these NFTs are randomly minted, and this is a chance for everyone to get a rare version. So due to the low price of these NFTs, if the rare version did not belong to you, it is still possible for you to mint the new NFTs.

Because this is an NFT in PFP format, you can put it on your avatar on Twitter or Instagram.

This project is a collaboration project and it is a Benefit for the owners of most Morixels to Collaborate with Morixels Designer.

You can read more information on Morixels website 👇

Website: https://morixels.com/

Twitter: @Morixels

by: @morteza_yousefy & @MontazeriAmin

Made in 2022

metadata.name: Swedish Forest #59
metadata.description:
If I had to choose a place where time was frozen and where I could contemplate the landscape for eternity this place would be a scandinavian forest.
I have been contemplating these kind of landscape for a very long time both in Sweden and in the Pyrenees where the ecosystem is very similar.
This project generates an illustration of a scandinavian forest in many different situations. At day and at night, in every season of the year, next to a lake or not, with steep hills or at the plains, snowing, with preponderance of some plant species over others, etc.
The artwork is also drawn in various paint modes and layouts.

The sun or the moon may be visible, the moon shows always the actual moon phase based on the current date.
The reflection on the lake is the fxhash morse endcoded.


Developed in vanilla js using svg and canvas
Rendering can be unresponsive on slow devices
Click or touch to switch to Parallax mode, just move the mouse or finger.


[S] Download in SVG format
[D] Download in PNG format

Features:

Layout: Landscape, Portrait, Square
PredominantSpecies: Blueberry, Lingonberry, Calluna, Rocks, None
Trees: Mixed, PinesAndFirs, Birches, None
Season: Spring, Summer, Fall, Winter
DayNight: Day, Night
PaintStyle: Normal, Stroke, Paint, WhiteOnBlack, BlackOnWhite
ColorStyle: Normal, Crazy
HasLake: True, False
HasTrees: None, Few, Many, Crowded

Created by Daniel Julià Lundgren, fxhash: danieljulia.tez, twitter: @daniel_julia. Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0, see LICENSE.txt for more information.

metadata.name: The Passing of Time #205
metadata.description:
To celebrate the one-year anniversary of fx(hash), an animated piece that both signifies and illustrates the passing of time. The generative code is derived from Before/After, but adds a unique animation algorithm that causes the artwork to organically expand and contract. The art adapts to different screen sizes but will work best in full-screen mode on a wide-screen monitor.

The Passing of Time is written in plain JavaScript, with the compute-intensive t-SNE transformation implemented in AssemblyScript and compiled to WebAssembly (WASM) for maximum performance. No external libraries have been used.

<space bar>: Pause the animation.
0, 1, 2, 3, 4: Resolution, from lowest (0) to highest (4); default is 2. Try to lower the resolution if the animation isn't smooth.

50% of primary proceeds will be donated to Tezos Ukraine, https://donate.tezos.org.ua/.

Author:
Claus O. Wilke
https://clauswilke.com/art
https://twitter.com/clauswilke

metadata.name: Vacuole #6
metadata.description:
Vacuole emerged from a cellular automaton sketch to which I come back from time to time to experiment with different rules and mechanisms.

To celebrate #fxhashturnsone, I wanted to look for alternative forms than the classical top-to-bottom/bottow-to-top scanline growing behaviour. Vocuole instead uses a grid of fields, where each field is initialized with different rules, growing directions and settings. The system combines two different variations: classical elementary cellular automata rules and a copy-pixel/plasma rule, which takes pixels from the neighborhood with a noise-controled offset like a stamp.


Donations:

All primary sales are split equally and donated to the Processing Foundation, thi.ng and
THREE.js.


Keyboard Shortcuts:

p: Pause/continue
s: Save as png
c: Switch between cover/contain


License: 

CC BY-NC-ND 4.0

metadata.name: Harmonies #263
metadata.description:
Harmonies is a color palette generator created for fxhash anniversary. The generator chooses from 7 possible color harmonies "Complementary, Split-Complementary, Analogous, Triadic, Tetradic, Square, Analogous and Monochromatic" to create harmonic color palettes. When i studied colors back in time, i used to take a color or a couple of colors and paint strokes on paper with watercolors to understand and learn how they stand out together. This piece is a result of those studies.

5 stroke compositions for 'Split-Complementary, Analogous and Triadic'
3 stroke compositions for 'Tetradic, Square and Monochromatic'
3 stroke compositions for 'Complementary'
2 color mods "Saturated and Muted' and 6 rendering methods for strokes 'Random Saturated, Random Brightness, Random Brightness & Saturation, Saturation Gradient, Brightness Gradient, Brightness & Saturation Gradient'

Save image by pressing 's'
Save colors as hex array ready to be used by pressing 'p'

Created with p5.js | Murat Atimtay 2022

metadata.name: fx(haish) / the Generator #191
metadata.description:
fx(haish) is my contribution to #fxhashturnsone
fx(haish) is not a finished product
fx(haish) is a co-creation experiment
fx(haish) is a fun exploration of a mixed GenAI process

fx(haish) is my Happy Birthday to fx(hash). 

Have fun, collectors!


// HOW TO PARTICIPATE

Step 1. Mint or collect “fx(haish) - the Generator”
Step 2. Visit https://www.arqtistic.com/fx(haish) to generate your “fx(haish) - The AI City” based on your mint. You have 20 tries.
Step 3. Await further instructions.


// FURTHER INFO

This algorithm has been designed to produce images which are suitable for the subsequent AI generation. The token consists of a random number of randomly placed and sized rectangles, filled with a noise gradient pattern. In short, Diffusion AI Models thrive on noise.

The AI generation uses Stable Diffusion 1.5 through an API designed by the 330ai team (@Pixelmindai). The WebUI has been developed by Nik0gda (@AntonCebanu2). AI Prompt has been designed (by me) to produce images of Cities, but you can possibly make it do other things, if you try hard enough.
